◆ binvert_limb

#define binvert_limb (   inv,
  n 
)
Value:
do { \
mp_limb_t __n = (n); \
mp_limb_t __inv; \
ASSERT ((__n & 1) == 1); \
\
__inv = binvert_limb_table[(__n/2) & 0x7F]; /* 8 */ \
if (GMP_NUMB_BITS > 8) __inv = 2 * __inv - __inv * __inv * __n; \
if (GMP_NUMB_BITS > 16) __inv = 2 * __inv - __inv * __inv * __n; \
if (GMP_NUMB_BITS > 32) __inv = 2 * __inv - __inv * __inv * __n; \
\
if (GMP_NUMB_BITS > 64) \
{ \
int __invbits = 64; \
do { \
__inv = 2 * __inv - __inv * __inv * __n; \
__invbits *= 2; \
} while (__invbits < GMP_NUMB_BITS); \
} \
\
ASSERT ((__inv * __n & GMP_NUMB_MASK) == 1); \
(inv) = __inv & GMP_NUMB_MASK; \
} while (0)

◆ invert_pi1

#define invert_pi1 (   dinv,
  d1,
  d0 
)
Value:
do { \
mp_limb_t _v, _p, _t1, _t0, _mask; \
invert_limb (_v, d1); \
_p = (d1) * _v; \
_p += (d0); \
if (_p < (d0)) \
{ \
_v--; \
_mask = -(mp_limb_t) (_p >= (d1)); \
_p -= (d1); \
_v += _mask; \
_p -= _mask & (d1); \
} \
umul_ppmm (_t1, _t0, d0, _v); \
_p += _t1; \
if (_p < _t1) \
{ \
_v--; \
if (UNLIKELY (_p >= (d1))) \
{ \
if (_p > (d1) || _t0 >= (d0)) \
_v--; \
} \
} \
(dinv).inv32 = _v; \
} while (0)

#define JACOBI_MOD_OR_MODEXACT_1_ODD (   result_bit1,

  a_ptr,
  a_size,
  b 
)
Value:

mp_size_t __a_size = (a_size); \

\

} \

(a_rem) = mpn_modexact_1_odd (__a_ptr, __a_size, __b); \
} \
} while (0)

◆ MPN_BSWAP

#define MPN_BSWAP (   dst,
  src,
  size 
)
Value:
do { \
mp_ptr __dst = (dst); \
mp_srcptr __src = (src); \
mp_size_t __size = (size); \
mp_size_t __i; \
ASSERT ((size) >= 0); \
ASSERT (MPN_SAME_OR_SEPARATE_P (dst, src, size)); \
CRAY_Pragma ("_CRI ivdep"); \
for (__i = 0; __i < __size; __i++) \
{ \
BSWAP_LIMB_FETCH (*__dst, __src); \
__dst++; \
__src++; \
} \
} while (0)

◆ MPN_BSWAP_REVERSE

#define MPN_BSWAP_REVERSE (   dst,
  src,
  size 
)
Value:

mp_ptr __dst = (dst); \
mp_size_t __size = (size); \
mp_srcptr __src = (src) + __size - 1; \

ASSERT (! MPN_OVERLAP_P (dst, size, src, size)); \
CRAY_Pragma ("_CRI ivdep"); \
for (__i = 0; __i < __size; __i++) \
{ \
BSWAP_LIMB_FETCH (*__dst, __src); \
__dst++; \
__src--; \
} \
} while (0)

◆ mpn_decr_u

#define mpn_decr_u (   p,
  incr 
)
Value:
do { \
mp_limb_t __x; \
mp_ptr __p = (p); \
if (__builtin_constant_p (incr) && (incr) == 1) \
{ \
while ((*(__p++))-- == 0) \
; \
} \
else \
{ \
__x = *__p; \
*__p = __x - (incr); \
if (__x < (incr)) \
while ((*(++__p))-- == 0) \
; \
} \
} while (0)

  incr 
)
Value:

mp_limb_t __x; \
mp_ptr __p = (p); \
if (__builtin_constant_p (incr) && (incr) == 1) \
{ \
while (++(*(__p++)) == 0) \
; \
} \
else \
{ \
__x = *__p + (incr); \
*__p = __x; \
if (__x < (incr)) \
while (++(*(++__p)) == 0) \
; \
} \
} while (0)

#define MPN_REVERSE (   dst,
  src,
  size 
)
Value:
do { \
mp_ptr __dst = (dst); \
mp_size_t __size = (size); \
mp_srcptr __src = (src) + __size - 1; \
mp_size_t __i; \

CRAY_Pragma ("_CRI ivdep"); \

*__dst = *__src; \
__dst++; \

} \
} while (0)

◆ MPN_SIZEINBASE

#define MPN_SIZEINBASE (   result,
  ptr,
  size,
  base 
)
Value:
do { \
int __lb_base, __cnt; \
size_t __totbits; \
\
ASSERT ((size) >= 0); \
ASSERT ((base) >= 2); \
ASSERT ((base) < numberof (mp_bases)); \
\
/* Special case for X == 0. */ \
if ((size) == 0) \
(result) = 1; \
else \
{ \
/* Calculate the total number of significant bits of X. */ \
count_leading_zeros (__cnt, (ptr)[(size)-1]); \
__totbits = (size_t) (size) * GMP_NUMB_BITS - (__cnt - GMP_NAIL_BITS);\
\
if (POW2_P (base)) \
{ \
__lb_base = mp_bases[base].big_base; \
(result) = (__totbits + __lb_base - 1) / __lb_base; \
} \
else \
{ \
DIGITS_IN_BASEGT2_FROM_BITS (result, __totbits, base); \
} \
} \
} while (0)

◆ MPN_SIZEINBASE_2EXP

#define MPN_SIZEINBASE_2EXP (   result,
  ptr,
  size,
  base2exp 
)
Value:
do { \
int __cnt; \
mp_bitcnt_t __totbits; \
ASSERT ((size) > 0); \
ASSERT ((ptr)[(size)-1] != 0); \
count_leading_zeros (__cnt, (ptr)[(size)-1]); \
__totbits = (mp_bitcnt_t) (size) * GMP_NUMB_BITS - (__cnt - GMP_NAIL_BITS); \
(result) = (__totbits + (base2exp)-1) / (base2exp); \
} while (0)

◆ MPQ_CHECK_FORMAT

#define MPQ_CHECK_FORMAT (   q)
Value:
do { \
MPZ_CHECK_FORMAT (mpq_numref (q)); \
MPZ_CHECK_FORMAT (mpq_denref (q)); \
ASSERT_ALWAYS (SIZ(mpq_denref(q)) >= 1); \
\
if (SIZ(mpq_numref(q)) == 0) \
{ \
/* should have zero as 0/1 */ \
ASSERT_ALWAYS (SIZ(mpq_denref(q)) == 1 \
&& PTR(mpq_denref(q))[0] == 1); \
} \
else \
{ \
/* should have no common factors */ \
mpz_t g; \
mpz_init (g); \
mpz_gcd (g, mpq_numref(q), mpq_denref(q)); \
ASSERT_ALWAYS (mpz_cmp_ui (g, 1) == 0); \
mpz_clear (g); \
} \
} while (0)

◆ NEG_MOD

#define NEG_MOD (   r,
  a,
  d 
)
Value:
do { \
ASSERT ((d) != 0); \
ASSERT_LIMB (a); \
ASSERT_LIMB (d); \
\
if ((a) <= (d)) \
{ \
/* small a is reasonably likely */ \
(r) = (d) - (a); \
} \
else \
{ \
unsigned __twos; \
mp_limb_t __dnorm; \
count_leading_zeros (__twos, d); \
__twos -= GMP_NAIL_BITS; \
__dnorm = (d) << __twos; \
(r) = ((a) <= __dnorm ? __dnorm : 2*__dnorm) - (a); \
} \
\
ASSERT_LIMB (r); \
} while (0)

◆ popc_limb

#define popc_limb (   result,
  input 
)
Value:
do { \
mp_limb_t __x = (input); \
__x -= (__x >> 1) & MP_LIMB_T_MAX/3; \
__x = ((__x >> 2) & MP_LIMB_T_MAX/5) + (__x & MP_LIMB_T_MAX/5); \
__x = ((__x >> 4) + __x) & MP_LIMB_T_MAX/17; \
__x = ((__x >> 8) + __x); \
__x = ((__x >> 16) + __x); \
__x = ((__x >> 32) + __x); \
(result) = __x & 0xff; \
} while (0)

#define udiv_qr_3by2 (   q,
  r1,
  r0,
  n2,
  n1,
  n0,
  d1,
  d0,
  dinv 
)
Value:

add_ssaaaa ((q), _q0, (q), _q0, (n2), (n1)); \
\

(r1) = (n1) - (d1) * (q); \
sub_ddmmss ((r1), (r0), (r1), (n0), (d1), (d0)); \
umul_ppmm (_t1, _t0, (d0), (q)); \
sub_ddmmss ((r1), (r0), (r1), (r0), _t1, _t0); \
(q)++; \
\

(q) += _mask; \
add_ssaaaa ((r1), (r0), (r1), (r0), _mask & (d1), _mask & (d0)); \

{ \
if ((r1) > (d1) || (r0) >= (d0)) \
{ \
(q)++; \
sub_ddmmss ((r1), (r0), (r1), (r0), (d1), (d0)); \
} \
} \
} while (0)
